<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFFF12EFF210F05D4A9A807" blockId="11.[130,777,1045,2028]" box="[132,393,1045,1072]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
DATA FOR 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFF520F06D4A9A807" authority="Latreille, 1810" box="[247,393,1046,1072]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">ORTHOPTERA</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAFB653AFFFFF12EFF210F24D059A907" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFFF12EFF210F24D477ABC6" blockId="11.[130,777,1045,2028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
One of us (AL) focused on 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFE110F24D627A864" authority="Acridomorpha. The" authorityName="Acridomorpha. The" box="[436,775,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera Acridomorpha.The</taxonomicName>
data summarized in Table 4 were used to produce distributional maps by species or groups of species, which proved reasonably accurate to interpret their distributions according to environmental data, or confirmed taxonomic hypotheses. 33 species of Caelifera have been recorded (Table 4). Among these, three Pamphaginae Burmeister, 1840, viz. 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFD330FE4D4A6A904" authority="(Bolivar, 1936)" baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Paracinipe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exarata">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFD330FE4D5F1A907" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Paracinipe exarata</emphasis>
(Bolivar, 1936)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFE310E03D411A964" authority="Morales Agacino, 1945" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1945" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauvarovia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendizabali">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFE310E03D785A907" box="[404,677,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Glauvarovia mendizabali</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFD0A0E03D411A964" author="Morales Agacino" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="310 - 339" part="20" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/148685" refId="ref12923" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1945 a. - Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 20 (3 - 4): 310 - 339. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 148685" title="Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental" type="journal article" year="1945">Morales Agacino, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFED50E23D466A947" authority="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps, 1968" authorityName="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saharae">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFED50E23D737A967" box="[368,535,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Glauia saharae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFD840E23D466A947" author="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="419 - 435" part="4" refId="ref13223" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. &amp; DESCAMPS M. 1968. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.) 4 (2): 419 - 435." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]" type="journal article" year="1968">Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, were found to be the southernmost of the 83 species of Pamphaginae known from North Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFF280E83D72CA987" author="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" box="[141,524,1427,1454]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="419 - 435" part="4" refId="ref13223" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. &amp; DESCAMPS M. 1968. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.) 4 (2): 419 - 435." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]" type="journal article" year="1968">Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFDBD0E84D7E5A987" author="Descamps" box="[536,709,1427,1454]" firstAuthor="Descamps" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="24 - 36" part="75" refId="ref11288" refString="DESCAMPS M. 1970. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. III. Acridoidea du Maroc saharien et Dericorythinae [Orth]. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 75 (1 - 2): 24 - 36." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. III. Acridoidea du Maroc saharien et Dericorythinae [Orth]." type="journal article" year="1970">Descamps 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFD6B0E83D447A9E7" author="Chobanov &amp; Massa" firstAuthor="Chobanov" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="409 - 425" part="5104" refId="ref10989" refString="CHOBANOV D. &amp; MASSA D. 2022. - On some Moroccan Pamphagidae, with the description of Euryparyphes (Orthoptera: Caelifera). Zootaxa 5104 (3): 409 - 425. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5104.3.3" title="On some Moroccan Pamphagidae, with the description of Euryparyphes (Orthoptera: Caelifera)" type="journal article" year="2022">Chobanov &amp; Massa 2022</bibRefCitation>
). All the four genera of 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFDC60EA3D627A9E7" authorityName="Jacobson &amp; Biancchi" authorityYear="1905" box="[611,775,1459,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dericorythidae</taxonomicName>
known from North Africa are present in the studied area, including one genus represented by a single endemic species, 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFF270D02D7A5AA07" authority="Morales Agacino, 1949" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1949" box="[130,645,1554,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Bolivaremia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domenechi">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFF270D02D45BAA06" box="[130,379,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Bolivaremia domenechi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFE270D02D7A5AA07" author="Morales Agacino" box="[386,645,1554,1581]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="145 - 174" part="25" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/151226" refId="ref13182" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1949. - Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 25: 145 - 174. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 151226" title="Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni" type="journal article" year="1949">Morales Agacino, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In contrast to the many species originating from the Mediterranean border of Sahara, only three taxa, 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFE4B0D42D4EFAAA6" authority="melanorhodon (Walker, 1829)" authorityName="melanorhodon (Walker" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Anacridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="melanorhodon" subSpecies="melanorhodon">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFE4B0D42D43BAAA6" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Anacridium melanorhodon melanorhodon</emphasis>
(Walker, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFE780D62D450AA86" authority="(Klug, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Poekilocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bufonius" subSpecies="hieroglyphicus">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFE780D62D5C0AA86" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Poekilocerus bufonius hieroglyphicus</emphasis>
(Klug, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFE070D82D59EAAE6" authority="Saussure, 1884" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Sphingonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFE070D82D780AA86" box="[418,672,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Sphingonotus canariensis</emphasis>
Saussure, 1884
</taxonomicName>
, are Sahelian species that extend occasionally to Rio de Oro. 
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFF7B0DC2D4CFAAC6" author="Morales Agacino" box="[222,495,1746,1773]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="310 - 339" part="20" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/148685" refId="ref12923" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1945 a. - Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 20 (3 - 4): 310 - 339. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 148685" title="Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental" type="journal article" year="1945" yearSuffix="a">Morales Agacino (1945a)</bibRefCitation>
collected eight nymphs of 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFF270DE2D4CDAB26" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[130,493,1778,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Poekilocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bufonius" subSpecies="hieroglyphicus">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFF270DE2D4CDAB26" box="[130,493,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Poekilocerus bufonius hieroglyphicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 1 ♂ and 1 ♀ nymphs (15. IV.1943) at Leglat = Derramán and 6 larvae (14.XII.1941) close to Zug. One of us (AG) observed also one larva at Derramán, west of Aousserd (22°36’N, 14°28’W; 360 m, 19-20. XII.2017). Such breeding, in localities where the obligatory host plant, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFE890C81D755AB81" authority="Aiton, 1811" authorityName="Aiton" authorityYear="1811" box="[300,629,1937,1963]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFE890C81D4C7AB81" box="[300,487,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Calotropis procera</emphasis>
Aïton, 1811
</taxonomicName>
, has not been found, is unlikely to result in fertile population (
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFD060CA2D466ABC1" author="Popov &amp; McE Kevan" firstAuthor="Popov" journalOrPublisher="Anti-Locust Bulletin" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 81" part="51" refId="ref13600" refString="POPOV B. G. &amp; MCE KEVAN D. K. 1979. - A revision of the genus Poekilocerus Audinet-Serville 1831 (Orthoptera: Acridoidae). Anti-Locust Bulletin 51: 1 - 81." title="A revision of the genus Poekilocerus Audinet-Serville 1831 (Orthoptera: Acridoidae)" type="journal article" year="1979">Popov &amp; McE Kevan 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="825E36B1FFFFF12EFCE60F05D059A907" blockId="11.[811,1456,1044,1326]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
We detailed below some of the questions that the inventories of Morales Agacino could help reanalysing, namely the synonymy between 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFC7E0F44D08FA844" authority="Morales Agacino, 1949" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1949" box="[987,1455,1108,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Pamphagulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mateui">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFC7E0F44D192A844" box="[987,1202,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Pamphagulus mateui</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFB120F44D08FA844" author="Morales Agacino" box="[1207,1455,1108,1134]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="145 - 174" part="25" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/151226" refId="ref13182" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1949. - Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 25: 145 - 174. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 151226" title="Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni" type="journal article" year="1949">Morales Agacino, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45E14D32FFFFF12EFCFC0F64D1E9A8A4" authority="Ramme, 1931" authorityName="Ramme" authorityYear="1931" box="[857,1225,1140,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Pamphagulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis id="B095EAA3FFFFF12EFCFC0F64D10EA8A4" box="[857,1070,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Pamphagulus vicinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E6704B40FFFFF12EFB960F65D1E9A8A4" author="Ramme" box="[1075,1225,1140,1167]" firstAuthor="Ramme" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="165 - 200" part="17" refId="ref13685" refString="RAMME W. A. T. 1931. - Beitrage zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Orthopterenfauna (Tettig. Et Acrid.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Berlin 17: 165 - 200." title="Beitrage zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Orthopterenfauna (Tettig. Et Acrid.)" type="journal article" year="1931">Ramme, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
